Best place for running inspiration.
🔻Apply to be featured🔻

node.text:
NEXEL LEVEL LEGS😳🔥Get your photos/videos posted in our account, apply for a feature visiting runningterritory.com/feature 👉🏼the link is in our bio: @RunningTerritory 

Save it for later!

Your results are tied to the small and consistent effort you put in on a daily basis. Learn to enjoy the process, be patient and only put POSITIVE energy into yourself! 💫 

METHOD ➡️ 12-15 reps per side | 4 sets | 30 secs rest 

📽 @realrubaali

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Running | Runners | Run on September 07, 2021 tagging @gigi_ultrarunner. May be an image of 1 person, standing and outdoors.

node.text:
by @Gigi_ultrarunner 💪 We can share your content in our page, check the link in our bio: @RunningTerritory to follow the process.

How does it feel to run 100 miles? Just look at my expression and you get your answer.

At 90 miles I was exhausted and in pain , but the determination to persevere had to prevail. It is a mind game. When your mind tells you "you are done", prove it wrong. 
You can always give it a little bit more. Shut your thoughts off and just keep moving. One step at a time. Stay focused. Stay in the moment. Trust yourself and your abilities, and always bring some extra snacks! 

Once you reach the finish line, everything subsides. No worries, no pain, no exhaustion .
Just a big smile and a happy heart. 

#ultrarunning #100miler #corunning

Never give up 👊 We can promote your photos in our account. Click the link in our bio for instructions: @RunningTerritory 

Leg day is always hard, and this set happened to have several of the hardest movements for me personally so I’m proud I knocked it out.

Managed to do my last set of squats at 135lbs which I’m super happy with after not squatting at all for a few months.

📽 @lauras_fit_to_live

node.text:
A hard core takes hard work! 💪We can post your photos and videos in our account, follow the link in our bio @RunningTerritory and we will select your pictures.

Get to it with this one. 🔥

Not so sure I’ll be able to get up, though, now that my core is ABSolutely destroyed from this workout. 😵 Wish me luck!

WORKOUT DEETS 👇

Compete 2-3 rounds of the following circuit using a dip bar:

1️⃣ HANGING FROGGERS
💥 8-10 reps

2️⃣ ALT. KNEE RAISE TWISTS
💥 5 reps each way

3️⃣ KNEE RAISE TO LEG EXTENSION
💥 8 reps

4️⃣ ALT. SINGLE LEG RAISE HOLDS
💥 5 reps each way

5️⃣ HANGING LEG RAISE HOLD
💥 Until failure

EXTRA CREDIT:

6️⃣ LEG RAISE PULL-UPS
💥 max effort

Rest 45 seconds between each exercise.

Tag someone who needs to try this one. 👊

Song: Without You by Avicii

📽 @clairepthomas

node.text:
"RUNNING TECHNIQUE" 💪 Apply to promote your content in our account, go to our link in bio: @RunningTerritory

I received a lot of questions about this subject after my latest videos. 🏃🏻‍♀️ A good running technique improves your sports performance, reduces the risk of injuries and, moreover, a technical runner does not tire as quickly. But remember, every body is different and the same approach doesn't work for everyone! I've listed some of my "favorite" running exercises below, you can see them in the video's (swipe left). I usually do these kind of exercises during warm-up for an interval or speed session. Do you sometimes do this kind of exercises?
.
.
1. Skipping with high knees
2. Butt kicks - high heels
3. Straight leg bounds
4. Running jumps (📹: @elien_janssen)
